title: Fragment of a Seal Stamp
description:
Dark green serpentine fragment of an oval stamp seal with a sunk relief scene of Hatshepsut, dressed as a woman, offering to Amun-Re. Only the heads of the figures are perserved, with their identifying inscriptions.

The top of the seal is a coiled uraeus with its head extending up and out at the front.
